Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @sweet potato{2}(chopped into 2cm chunks) (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle over half the @curry powder mix{1/2%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While everything cooks, halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} stems lengthways, then cut them into thirds. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Drain the @king prawns{150%g}.

Once hot, add the prawns and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Next, stir in the @korma curry paste{50%g}, garlic and remaining @curry powder mix{1/2%sachet}. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Stir in the broccoli, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water for the curry{100%ml} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, lower the heat, cover with a lid and simmer until the broccoli is just tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Next, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @mango chutney{40%g}. Bring back to the boil, then remove from the heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the sweet potato is roasted, stir it through the curry. Return the pan to the heat to warm through. Add a splash of @water{a splash} if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your plates, then top with your korma style curry. Enjoy!